// A `#foreign` decl IS a real C-ABI global, so its symbol stays reachable bare (`net_listen(...)`)
// as a C-interop affordance, in addition to the idiomatic qualified `net.net_listen(...)`. (By
// contrast, pure-Arche module members are renamed to their qualified identity `net.<name>` and are
// strictly qualified-only — a bare reference to one does NOT resolve.) Qualified is the recommended
// API; this pins that the raw C symbol remains linkable for interop.
// RUN: %arche check %s
#import { net }
main :: proc() {
  net.net_listen(8080)(s:); // idiomatic: qualified
  net_listen(8081)(s2:); // raw C symbol still resolves (interop affordance)
  net.net_close(move s);
  net.net_close(move s2);
}
